# Licensing

This repository is the **Conspiracy LARP Dungeon Master's Guide**: a manual (the prose in
`src/pack/`) plus the tooling that renders it (`src/build/`, `src/theme/`, and the rest of
the code). The two are licensed differently, each under the copyleft licence meant for its
kind of work. Both are strong copyleft: share, adapt, and build on them, but keep
adaptations as free as you received them.

## The guide — the prose in `src/pack/`

Licensed under the **Creative Commons Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International** licence
(CC BY-SA 4.0).

- SPDX: `CC-BY-SA-4.0`
- Full text: <https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/legalcode>

You may copy, redistribute, and adapt it for any purpose, including commercially, provided
you give appropriate attribution and license your adaptations **of this guide** under the
same terms.

## The tooling — `src/build/`, `src/theme/`, and other code

Licensed under the **GNU General Public License, version 3 or later** (GPL-3.0-or-later).

- SPDX: `GPL-3.0-or-later`
- Full text: <https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt>

## What these licences do NOT cover: your game is yours

This applies **only to the guide and its tooling**. The properties you create for the game —
your nodes, sites, filings, characters, stories, screenshots, and every artifact you build by
following this guide — **remain your own, under whatever copyright and licence you choose,
even though the guide inspired them.**

ShareAlike reaches adaptations of the guide's *own text*. It does not reach the fiction you
make with it. You owe attribution if you reproduce or adapt this guide; you owe it nothing for
the world you build after reading it. The guide is given freely so the idea can spread; the
worlds people make with it are theirs.

